Author: blackjok3r#3181
Content: Since its so easy to move computationally heavy things into the core ... and its 1000x faster than a script, anything I cna think of that can go in there, I have been slowly moving into it.

Author: blackjok3r#3181
Content:
bash + jq = slow
custom RPC's + python = very fast

Author: blackjok3r#3181
Content: Most things will stay as scripts, but if there is heavy sorting and calcuation's for something, its 100x better to make a c++ function every time.

Author: ComputerGenie 游놊游낖游닉#7004
Content:
`bash + jq = slow
custom RPC's + python = very fast`
agree, but my only comment would be:
just make sure you don't end up with a 100MB client just for the sake of saving users from 30 seconds of runtime for 100kB worth of scripting
